---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'; // Changed from BaseLayout to Base
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content'; // Import getCollection if using content collections
// Or use Astro.glob if using markdown files directly in pages/posts
const allPosts = (await Astro.glob('./posts/*.md')).sort(
  (a, b) => new Date(b.frontmatter.date).valueOf() - new Date(a.frontmatter.date).valueOf()
);

// Function to get N recent posts
function getRecentPosts(arr, n) {
  return arr.slice(0, n);
}

// Get 3 recent posts
const suggestedPosts = getRecentPosts(allPosts, 3);

const pageTitle = "About Trained Tails | Dog Training Expertise"; // Define a title
---
<Base title={pageTitle}> {/* Use Base layout and pass the title */}
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12"> {/* Increased max-width slightly */}
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-6 text-center"> {/* Adjusted heading size */}
      My Story & The Heart Behind Trained Tails
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
      Hello and welcome to Trained Tails! I'm so thrilled you've stopped by. My name is Kerem, and I'm the passionate dog lover and training enthusiast behind this blog. My journey into the fascinating world of dog behavior and positive training started right here in beautiful Istanbul, and it's been an incredible adventure ever since. Trained Tails was born from a simple desire: to share effective, kind, and science-backed training methods to help dog owners build truly amazing, trusting relationships with their canine companions.
    </p>

    <img src="/assets/images/about-trainer.jpg" alt="[Your Name], founder of Trained Tails, smiling warmly." class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl my-8 shadow-lg max-w-md mx-auto" loading="lazy" />
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4 mt-12">My Journey to Positive Training</h2> {/* Adjusted heading size */}

    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-6">
      Like many people, my deep dive into dog training began with my own dogs. I faced challenges – recall struggles in bustling Istanbul parks, leash pulling on historical streets, the usual puppy antics! Initially, I explored various methods, but something didn't feel quite right with the more traditional, correction-based approaches. It wasn't fostering the partnership I craved.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
      That led me down the path of positive reinforcement and science-based training. Discovering how dogs *really* learn, understanding their body language, and focusing on rewarding desired behaviors instead of punishing unwanted ones was revolutionary for me. It wasn't just more effective; it felt better, building communication and joy rather than conflict. Since then, I've dedicated myself to learning everything I can – constantly reading research, attending workshops [mention certifications if applicable, e.g., "earning my certification"], and working hands-on with dogs of all breeds and temperaments, including volunteering with some wonderful local Istanbul rescues. This experience solidified my belief that kindness and science are the keys to unlocking a dog's potential.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-4 mb-12 bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-lg ring-1 ring-slate-200 dark:ring-slate-700"> {/* Adjusted background */}
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 mb-3">What Trained Tails Believes In:</h3> {/* Adjusted heading level */}
      <ul class="list-none space-y-3">
        <li class="flex items-start">
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2 mt-1 text-emerald-500 flex-shrink-0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2.5" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12a9 9 0 1 1-18 0 9 9 0 0 1 18 0Z" /></svg>
          <span class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200"><strong class="font-semibold">Positive Reinforcement First:</strong> We focus on rewarding good choices and building motivation through kindness. No fear, force, or intimidation here.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
           <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2 mt-1 text-emerald-500 flex-shrink-0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2.5" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12a9 9 0 1 1-18 0 9 9 0 0 1 18 0Z" /></svg>
          <span class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200"><strong class="font-semibold">Science-Based & Effective:</strong> Our methods are grounded in the latest understanding of animal behavior and learning theory.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start">
           <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2 mt-1 text-emerald-500 flex-shrink-0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2.5" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12a9 9 0 1 1-18 0 9 9 0 0 1 18 0Z" /></svg>
          <span class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200"><strong class="font-semibold">Building Strong Bonds:</strong> Training should enhance your relationship, building trust and mutual understanding.</span>
        </li>
         <li class="flex items-start">
           <svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2 mt-1 text-emerald-500 flex-shrink-0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2.5" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12a9 9 0 1 1-18 0 9 9 0 0 1 18 0Z" /></svg>
          <span class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200"><strong class="font-semibold">Practical & Realistic:</strong> Providing tips and solutions that work in real life, for real dog owners.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">What You'll Find on the Blog</h2> {/* Adjusted heading size */}

    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
      Here at Trained Tails, I share everything I've learned (and am still learning!). Expect to find practical training guides, deep dives into dog behavior topics, tips for troubleshooting common problems, personal insights from my experiences, and hopefully, a dose of inspiration. Whether you're navigating puppyhood, working on basic manners, or just want to understand your dog better, my goal is to provide clear, actionable, and positive advice.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">Meet My Co-Pilot(s)</h2> {/* Adjusted heading size */}
     <img src="/assets/images/about-dogs.jpg" alt="[Dog's Name(s)], the inspiration behind Trained Tails." class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl my-8 shadow-lg max-w-lg mx-auto" loading="lazy" />
    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
      Of course, I couldn't do this without my own furry inspiration, Pera. He constantly teach me new things about patience, communication, and the sheer joy dogs bring to our lives. You'll probably see [him/her/them] pop up in examples and stories throughout the blog!
    </p>


    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">Let's Connect!</h2> {/* Adjusted heading size */}

    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
      Thank you so much for visiting Trained Tails. I truly believe that training is a journey, not just a destination, and it's one best traveled with understanding and kindness. I hope you find the resources here helpful! Feel free to explore the posts, and let's make the world a better place for our dogs, one positive interaction at a time.
    </p>

  </div>

  <!-- Suggested Posts Section -->
  {suggestedPosts.length > 0 && (
    <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 mt-12 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-100 mb-8 text-center">Recent Blog Posts</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-6 sm:gap-8 grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {suggestedPosts.map(post => (
          <article class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl shadow-md overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow flex flex-col">
            {post.frontmatter.image && (
              <a href={post.url} class="block">
                <img src={post.frontmatter.image} alt={post.frontmatter.title + " preview"} class="w-full h-40 object-cover" loading="lazy" />
              </a>
            )}
            <div class="p-4 sm:p-5 flex flex-col flex-grow">
              <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold mt-1 mb-2 flex-grow dark:text-white">
                <a href={post.url} class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">{post.frontmatter.title}</a>
              </h3>
              <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-3 text-sm line-clamp-3">{post.frontmatter.description}</p>
              <div class="mt-auto">
                 <a href={post.url} class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline text-sm font-medium">Read more →</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>
  )}
</Base>
